                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.12370/2606.12370v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 3:Decomposition of acceptance length changes during RL training.Δ​α\\Delta\\alpha(total, gray) is decomposed into an entropy-driven componentΔ​αentropy=b⋅(ℋt−ℋ0)\\Delta\\alpha_{\\mathrm{entropy}}=b\\cdot(\\mathcal{H}_{t}-\\mathcal{H}_{0})(orange) and a draft–target mismatch componentΔ​αmismatch\\Delta\\alpha_{\\mathrm{mismatch}}(green).\nUnder target-only sampling, both entropy increase and growing mismatch contribute to acceptance degradation.\nUnder rejection sampling with CE loss, the degradation is almost entirely entropy-driven, with mismatch remaining near zero.\nRS with TV loss shows near-zero change across all components, confirming the stability of TV-trained drafts.",
